{"type":"message","id":"33593e53","parentId":"c75327bd","timestamp":"2026-03-09T16:18:14.711Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2AFAA6C500969CFA0A1B\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+971504042000\",\n  \"sender\": \"Golden Cruise Restaurant\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Golden Cruise Restaurant (+971504042000)\",\n  \"id\": \"+971504042000\",\n  \"name\": \"Golden Cruise Restaurant\",\n  \"e164\": \"+971504042000\"\n}\n```\n\nYou are performing a FULL SYSTEM AUDIT of this project.\n\nDo NOT only analyze OpenClaw configuration.  \nAudit the entire architecture and workspace, including integrations with XMAD controller, databases, orchestrators, agents, memory systems, and voice modules.\n\nThe goal is to understand what this project actually does, how components interact, and what can be optimized or fixed.\n\n---\n\n# 1. PROJECT DISCOVERY\n\nFirst map the entire project.\n\nScan and analyze:\n\n- ~/.openclaw\n- ~/Desktop/xmad-control-center\n- workspace/\n- scripts/\n- memory/\n- agents/\n- orchestrator configs\n- database files\n- environment configs\n\nIdentify:\n\nвҖў Main architecture  \nвҖў System purpose  \nвҖў Major components  \nвҖў Integration points\n\nOutput a system architecture diagram in text.\n\nExample:\n\nUser вҶ’ WhatsApp вҶ’ OpenClaw Gateway вҶ’ Nova Agent вҶ’ Guardian Orchestrator вҶ’ Skills/Tools вҶ’ XMAD Controller вҶ’ Database\n\n---\n\n# 2. OPENCLAW CORE AUDIT\n\nCheck the entire OpenClaw runtime:\n\nFiles to inspect:\n\n- openclaw.json\n- auth-profiles.json\n- watchdog.sh\n- start scripts\n- logs\n- plugins\n- skills\n\nReport:\n\nвҖў enabled tools  \nвҖў disabled tools  \nвҖў sandbox status  \nвҖў execution permissions  \nвҖў gateway status  \nвҖў memory limits  \nвҖў runtime environment\n\nAlso check:\n\nвҖў tool conflicts  \nвҖў security risks  \nвҖў redundant modules  \nвҖў unused plugins\n\n---\n\n# 3. XMAD CONTROL CENTER ANALYSIS\n\nAnalyze the XMAD controller project.\n\nFocus on:\n\n- server.js\n- controller modules\n- integrated APIs\n- UI layer\n- automation logic\n\nDetermine:\n\nвҖў how XMAD communicates with OpenClaw  \nвҖў which tools or APIs are shared  \nвҖў which components control agents\n\nExplain clearly:\n\nWhat is XMAD responsible for?\n\nExamples to check:\n\nвҖў device control  \nвҖў automation hub  \nвҖў AI command center  \nвҖў monitoring dashboard\n\n---\n\n# 4. AGENT ORCHESTRATION\n\nSearch the project for:\n\n- guardian\n- orchestrator\n- agents\n- planner\n- controller\n- automation\n\nIdentify:\n\nвҖў Guardian orchestrator  \nвҖў Nova agent role  \nвҖў task delegation system  \nвҖў agent communication\n\nExplain the multi-agent architecture.\n\nExample:\n\nPlanner agent  \nExecutor agent  \nResearch agent  \nController agent\n\nAlso detect if unused agents exist.\n\n---\n\n# 5. MEMORY SYSTEM\n\nAudit all memory sources:\n\n- SQLite\n- markdown memory\n- vector DB\n- LanceDB\n- logs\n- persona files\n\nFiles to check:\n\nmemory/\nMEMORY.md\nSOUL.md\nIDENTITY.md\nmain.sqlite\n\nReport:\n\nвҖў memory type  \nвҖў memory size  \nвҖў retention system  \nвҖў pruning logic  \nвҖў context limits\n\nIdentify missing improvements such as:\n\nvector memory  \nsemantic recall  \nknowledge graph\n\n---\n\n# 6. DATABASE SYSTEM\n\nSearch for database integrations.\n\nPossible systems:\n\nSQLite  \nLanceDB  \nJSON storage  \nPostgres  \nRedis\n\nReport:\n\nвҖў which DBs exist  \nвҖў which are active  \nвҖў which are planned but not enabled\n\nExplain their purpose.\n\n---\n\n# 7. AUTOMATION SYSTEM\n\nSearch for automation components:\n\ncron  \nwatchdog  \ntask scheduler  \njob runner  \nhealth monitor\n\nExplain differences between:\n\nwatchdog  \ncron  \nconnection monitor\n\nList all scheduled or automatic processes.\n\n---\n\n# 8. VOICE SYSTEM\n\nAudit voice stack.\n\nCheck:\n\nSTT  \nTTS  \naudio pipelines\n\nDetermine:\n\nвҖў which voice engines are active  \nвҖў memory usage  \nвҖў duplication issues  \nвҖў whether OpenClaw already handles STT\n\nRecommend optimizations for low RAM machines.\n\n---\n\n# 9. PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS\n\nMeasure:\n\nвҖў memory usage  \nвҖў CPU usage  \nвҖў I/O load  \nвҖў background processes  \nвҖў cache usage\n\nIdentify:\n\nвҖў heavy modules  \nвҖў unnecessary background tasks  \nвҖў redundant services\n\nRecommend improvements for older Macs (8GB RAM).\n\n---\n\n# 10. SECURITY REVIEW\n\nCheck:\n\nвҖў sandbox status  \nвҖў shell access permissions  \nвҖў exposed ports  \nвҖў API key storage  \nвҖў external integrations\n\nReport any risk areas.\n\n---\n\n# 11. MISSING FEATURES\n\nCompare the system against modern agent architectures.\n\nCheck if missing:\n\nвҖў vector memory  \nвҖў browser automation  \nвҖў agent planner  \nвҖў task scheduling  \nвҖў observability tools  \nвҖў autonomous workflows\n\n---\n\n# 12. PROJECT PURPOSE\n\nAfter the audit, explain:\n\nWhat is the overall goal of this project?\n\nPossible categories:\n\nAI assistant  \nAI automation system  \nAI command center  \nmulti-agent platform  \nbusiness automation\n\nExplain how OpenClaw and XMAD work together.\n\n---\n\n# 13. FINAL REPORT\n\nProvide a structured report with sections:\n\n1. Architecture map  \n2. Component list  \n3. Tool analysis  \n4. Memory analysis  \n5. Database analysis  \n6. Agent system  \n7. Performance issues  \n8. Security issues  \n9. Missing features  \n10. Optimization recommendations\n\nBe extremely detailed.\n\nAlso identify dead code, unused tools, and incomplete features."}],"timestamp":1773073094704}}
