{"type":"message","id":"ce54a6e5","parentId":"11b22ecb","timestamp":"2026-03-11T15:40:05.587Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5ed110614e954a4fa970af89","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"total 56\ndrwxr-xr-x  3 ahmadabdullah  staff     96 Mar 10 22:05 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  6 ahmadabdullah  staff    192 Mar 10 02:35 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 ahmadabdullah  staff  26067 Mar 11 01:52 watchdog.log"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":307,"aggregated":"total 56\ndrwxr-xr-x  3 ahmadabdullah  staff     96 Mar 10 22:05 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  6 ahmadabdullah  staff    192 Mar 10 02:35 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 ahmadabdullah  staff  26067 Mar 11 01:52 watchdog.log","cwd":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773243605583}}
{"type":"message","id":"56e08f52","parentId":"ce54a6e5","timestamp":"2026-03-11T15:40:05.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a760b8622abb437ba75828ae","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"total 8\ndrwxr-xr-x  3 ahmadabdullah  staff   96 Mar 10 22:05 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  6 ahmadabdullah  staff  192 Mar 10 02:35 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 ahmadabdullah  staff  189 Mar 11 01:52 status.json"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":221,"aggregated":"total 8\ndrwxr-xr-x  3 ahmadabdullah  staff   96 Mar 10 22:05 .\ndrwxr-xr-x  6 ahmadabdullah  staff  192 Mar 10 02:35 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 ahmadabdullah  staff  189 Mar 11 01:52 status.json","cwd":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773243605806}}
{"type":"message","id":"87e41215","parentId":"56e08f52","timestamp":"2026-03-11T15:40:06.087Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5486644009bf420ab5796a8e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Nova Self-Audit Prompt\n\nSend this message to Nova via WhatsApp to trigger a full system self-audit:\n\n---\n\n## Full Audit Command\n\n```\nNova, perform a complete self-audit and report everything about yourself:\n\n1. **CONFIG AUDIT**\n   - Read your ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json and list ALL active settings\n   - Report: model, memory limits, heartbeat, hooks, plugins enabled\n   - Show NODE_OPTIONS and any env vars configured\n\n2. **CONNECTION STATUS**\n   - Check WhatsApp connection status\n   - Verify gateway is running on port 18789\n   - Test /health endpoint and report result\n\n3. **ACCESS & PERMISSIONS**\n   - List what tools you have access to (bash, read, write, web, etc.)\n   - Report your workspace directory\n   - Check if elevated mode is enabled\n\n4. **VOICE CONFIG (TTS/STT)**\n   - Report your TTS provider setting\n   - Report STT configuration\n   - Confirm if using native API-side or local processing\n\n5. **MEMORY & BRAIN**\n   - List all files in ~/.openclaw/memory/\n   - Read and share your persona file (if exists)\n   - Show any brain/knowledge files loaded\n   - Report current session memory count\n\n6. **HEARTBEAT & HEALTH**\n   - Show your heartbeat interval setting\n   - Report last heartbeat time\n   - Show current memory usage (RSS in MB)\n\n7. **OPTIMIZATIONS**\n   - List all optimizations currently applied\n   - Report compaction settings\n   - Show context pruning configuration\n\n8. **PLUGINS & SKILLS**\n   - List enabled plugins\n   - Show loaded skills\n   - Report any disabled features\n\nFormat your response as a structured report. Be thorough - I want to see everything.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Health Check (shorter version)\n\n```\nNova quick check: Report your current status:\n- PID and memory usage\n- WhatsApp connected? (yes/no)\n- Model in use\n- Read your persona from ~/.openclaw/memory/ and tell me who you are\n- List your active brain files\n```\n\n---\n\n## Brain Dump (memory/persona only)\n\n```\nNova, share your brain:\n1. Read all files in ~/.openclaw/memory/\n2. Tell me your persona and identity\n3. Summarize what you know about me\n4. List any saved memories or knowledge\n```"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":224,"aggregated":"# Nova Self-Audit Prompt\n\nSend this message to Nova via WhatsApp to trigger a full system self-audit:\n\n---\n\n## Full Audit Command\n\n```\nNova, perform a complete self-audit and report everything about yourself:\n\n1. **CONFIG AUDIT**\n   - Read your ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json and list ALL active settings\n   - Report: model, memory limits, heartbeat, hooks, plugins enabled\n   - Show NODE_OPTIONS and any env vars configured\n\n2. **CONNECTION STATUS**\n   - Check WhatsApp connection status\n   - Verify gateway is running on port 18789\n   - Test /health endpoint and report result\n\n3. **ACCESS & PERMISSIONS**\n   - List what tools you have access to (bash, read, write, web, etc.)\n   - Report your workspace directory\n   - Check if elevated mode is enabled\n\n4. **VOICE CONFIG (TTS/STT)**\n   - Report your TTS provider setting\n   - Report STT configuration\n   - Confirm if using native API-side or local processing\n\n5. **MEMORY & BRAIN**\n   - List all files in ~/.openclaw/memory/\n   - Read and share your persona file (if exists)\n   - Show any brain/knowledge files loaded\n   - Report current session memory count\n\n6. **HEARTBEAT & HEALTH**\n   - Show your heartbeat interval setting\n   - Report last heartbeat time\n   - Show current memory usage (RSS in MB)\n\n7. **OPTIMIZATIONS**\n   - List all optimizations currently applied\n   - Report compaction settings\n   - Show context pruning configuration\n\n8. **PLUGINS & SKILLS**\n   - List enabled plugins\n   - Show loaded skills\n   - Report any disabled features\n\nFormat your response as a structured report. Be thorough - I want to see everything.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Health Check (shorter version)\n\n```\nNova quick check: Report your current status:\n- PID and memory usage\n- WhatsApp connected? (yes/no)\n- Model in use\n- Read your persona from ~/.openclaw/memory/ and tell me who you are\n- List your active brain files\n```\n\n---\n\n## Brain Dump (memory/persona only)\n\n```\nNova, share your brain:\n1. Read all files in ~/.openclaw/memory/\n2. Tell me your persona and identity\n3. Summarize what you know about me\n4. List any saved memories or knowledge\n```","cwd":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773243606079}}
{"type":"message","id":"453275c6","parentId":"87e41215","timestamp":"2026-03-11T15:40:19.325Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n# рҹ“Ғ **OPENCLAW IN XMAD CONTROL CENTER**\n\nFound it! XMAD has some OpenClaw-related files:\n\n## **XMAD OpenClaw Directory**\n```\n~/Desktop/xmad-control-center/openclaw/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ logs/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ (empty - 0 files)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ watchdog/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ watchdog.log (26KB)\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ status.json (189B)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ nova-self-audit-prompt.md\nв””в”Җв”Җ (no actual OpenClaw installation)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **рҹ“Ҡ WHAT'S IN XMAD**\n\n| File | Size | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| **watchdog.log** | 26KB | OpenClaw watchdog logs |\n| **status.json** | 189B | Watchdog status |\n| **nova-self-audit-prompt.md** | 2KB | Audit prompt template |\n\n---\n\n## **рҹ”Қ ANALYSIS**\n\n**XMAD Control Center does NOT contain OpenClaw installation.**\n\nIt only has:\n1. **Watchdog logs** - Monitoring OpenClaw (which runs elsewhere)\n2. **Audit prompts** - Templates for triggering audits\n3. **API handlers** - To control OpenClaw remotely\n\n**XMAD is a dashboard/controller** - it monitors and controls OpenClaw, but doesn't contain it.\n\n---\n\n## **рҹ“Қ TRUE OPENCLAW LOCATIONS**\n\n```\n~/.openclaw/              вҶҗ Main installation (20MB)\n~/.bun/bin/openclaw       вҶҗ Binary\n~/Library/LaunchAgents/   вҶҗ Auto-start\n```\n\n**XMAD just talks to OpenClaw** via:\n- Port 18789 (gateway)\n- Shell commands (`openclaw start/stop`)\n- File monitoring (`~/.openclaw/logs/`)\n\n---\n\nEverything is clean! XMAD is just a remote control for OpenClaw, not a duplicate installation."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":67266,"output":403,"cacheRead":22144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89813,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773243606084}}
