tart: cd /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/ignore/voice-microservices/tts-chatterbox && ./start-all.sh\nвң… Kokoro TTS - already available at port 8002\n   Start: cd /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/ignore/voice-microservices/tts-kokoro && ./start-all.sh\n\nвң… Voice integration setup complete!\n\nрҹ“Ғ Files created:\n   /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/xmad-control-center/voice/voice-client.js\n   /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/xmad-control-center/voice/start-voice-services.sh\n   /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/xmad-control-center/voice/README.md\n\nрҹҡҖ To start voice services:\n   /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/xmad-control-center/voice/start-voice-services.sh\n\nвҡ пёҸ  Note: Voice services run independently from OpenClaw\n   They will NOT impact OpenClaw/WhatsApp memory usage","cwd":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773247349420}}
{"type":"message","id":"04be77bd","parentId":"156f710b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T16:42:51.846Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a summary document:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a345c4de68554b50ad3dde68","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# вң… Backup, Voice Integration & API Keys - Complete\n\n**Date**: 2026-03-11 20:45\n**Status**: рҹҺү All tasks complete\n\n---\n\n## 1. вң… BACKUP COMPLETE\n\n**Backup Created**: `~/Desktop/openclaw-backup-20260311-204146.tar.gz`\n**Size**: 83KB\n**Contains**:\n- ~/.openclaw/ (full installation)\n- ~/Desktop/xmad-control-center/ (dashboard)\n\n**To Restore**:\n```bash\ncd ~/\ntar -xzf ~/Desktop/openclaw-backup-20260311-204146.tar.gz\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. вң… VOICE INTEGRATION SETUP\n\n### Selected Providers (Based on PROVIDER_SELECTION.md)\n\n**STT (Speech-to-Text)**:\n- **SenseVoice** (Port 50000)\n  - 50+ languages\n  - Emotion detection\n  - Best multilingual support\n\n**TTS (Text-to-Speech)**:\n- **Chatterbox** (Port 8000) вӯҗ Primary\n  - Best quality overall\n  - Voice cloning\n  - Beats ElevenLabs in blind tests\n  \n- **Kokoro** (Port 8002) - Secondary\n  - Ultra-fast (96x real-time)\n  - Best for real-time apps\n\n### Why These Providers?\n\n**Criteria**:\n1. вң… **Quality**: Chatterbox is best-in-class\n2. вң… **Speed**: Kokoro is 96x real-time\n3. вң… **Cost**: Both are FREE (local inference)\n4. вң… **Privacy**: Run locally, no cloud APIs\n5. вң… **Memory**: Separate from OpenClaw (no impact)\n\n### What Was Created\n\n**Location**: `~/Desktop/xmad-control-center/voice/`\n\n1. **voice-client.js** - JavaScript client for XMAD dashboard\n2. **start-voice-services.sh** - Start all voice microservices\n3. **README.md** - Complete documentation\n\n### How to Use\n\n**Start voice services**:\n```bash\n~/Desktop/xmad-control-center/voice/start-voice-services.sh\n```\n\n**Or start individually**:\n```bash\ncd ~/Desktop/ignore/voice-microservices/stt-sensevoice && ./start-all.sh\ncd ~/Desktop/ignore/voice-microservices/tts-chatterbox && ./start-all.sh\ncd ~/Desktop/ignore/voice-microservices/tts-kokoro && ./start-all.sh\n```\n\n### Integration with XMAD Dashboard\n\nThe voice services run **completely independently** from OpenClaw:\n- вң… **Separate processes** - No shared memory\n- вң… **Local only** - No cloud API costs\n- вң… **High quality** - Chatterbox beats ElevenLabs\n- вң… **Fast** - Kokoro is 96x real-time\n- вң… **No impact** on OpenClaw/WhatsApp memory\n\n---\n\n## 3. вң… API KEYS (SSOT - Single Source of Truth)\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\nmacOS Keychain (Master Backup)\n       вҶ“\nInfisical (Runtime Provider)\n       вҶ“\nProjects (No secrets, all injected)\n```\n\n### Key Locations\n\n**Infisical**:\n- Project ID: `3f265951-5e47-4460-88c1-ad9bee65b1ac`\n- Environment: `dev`, `staging`, `prod`\n- 13+ secrets available\n\n**macOS Keychain**:\n- All secrets stored with `SSOT_*` prefix\n- Hardware-backed by Apple Secure Enclave\n- Root of trust for all secrets\n\n### Best Practices (From SSOT_API_KEYS_GUIDE.md)\n\n**DO**:\n- вң… Use Infisical CLI for runtime injection\n- вң… Store master copies in macOS Keychain\n- вң… Use `SSOT_*` prefix for all keys\n- вң… Never hardcode secrets in code\n\n**DON'T**:\n- вқҢ No .env files in projects\n- вқҢ No hardcoded secrets\n- вқҢ No secrets in git repositories\n\n### How to Use Keys in Scripts\n\n**Infisical CLI**:\n```bash\n# Inject all secrets into environment\neval $(infisical run --env=dev -- your-command)\n\n# Or inject specific secrets\nexport GROQ_API_KEY=$(infisical get --env=dev GROQ_API_KEY)\n```\n\n**From macOS Keychain**:\n```bash\n# Get SSOT_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY\nsecurity find-generic-password -w -s \"SSOT_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY\"\n```\n\n### Available Keys\n\n**From the guide**, these keys are configured:\n- `SSOT_DEEPGRAM_API_KEY` - Deepgram STT\n- `SSOT_ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` - ElevenLabs TTS\n- `SSOT_GROQ_API_KEY` - Groq (Whisper STT + LLM)\n- `SSOT_GEMINI_API_KEY` - Gemini LLM\n- `SSOT_ZAI_API_KEY` - z.ai (GLM models)\n- Plus 8 more...\n\n**Note**: Voice microservices use local inference, so no API keys needed for STT/TTS!\n\n---\n\n## рҹ“Ҡ Current Status\n\n### Backup\n- вң… Created: 83KB tar.gz\n- вң… Location: ~/Desktop/\n- вң… Contains: OpenClaw + XMAD\n\n### Voice Services\n- вң… Setup complete\n- вң… Scripts created\n- вң… Ready to start\n- вҸёпёҸ Not running yet (user needs to start)\n\n### API Keys\n- вң… Documented in SSOT_API_KEYS_GUIDE.md\n- вң… Stored in Infisical + Keychain\n- вң… No hardcoded secrets\n- вң… Ready for use\n\n---\n\n## рҹҺҜ Next Steps\n\n### 1. Start Voice Services (Optional)\n```bash\n~/Desktop/xmad-control-center/voice/start-voice-services.sh\n```\n\n### 2. Update XMAD Dashboard (Optional)\n- Add voice controls from `voice-client.js`\n- Connect to local microservices\n- No impact on OpenClaw\n\n### 3. Use API Keys (When Needed)\n- Read `SSOT_API_KEYS_GUIDE.md`\n- Use Infisical CLI for injection\n- Never hardcode secrets\n\n---\n\n## рҹ“Ғ Files Created\n\n**In `~/Desktop/xmad-control-center/`**:\n1. `voice/voice-client.js` - Voice API client\n2. `voice/start-voice-services.sh` - Startup script\n3. `voice/README.md` - Voice documentation\n4. `setup-voice-integration.sh` - Setup script (can delete)\n\n**Documentation** (already exists):\n- `~/Desktop/important-docs/SSOT_API_KEYS_GUIDE.md`\n- `~/Desktop/ignore/voice-microservices/PROVIDER_SELECTION.md`\n\n---\n\n## вҡ пёҸ Important Notes\n\n### Voice Services & OpenClaw Memory\n\n**Voice services run INDEPENDENTLY from OpenClaw**:\n- Separate processes\n- Separate memory allocation\n- No impact on OpenClaw's 768MB limit\n- OpenClaw continues working normally\n\n**RAM Usage** (when voice services running):\n- SenseVoice STT: ~500MB\n- Chatterbox TTS: ~1GB\n- Kokoro TTS: ~200MB\n- **Total**: ~1.7GB (separate from OpenClaw)\n\n**Recommendation**:\n- Start voice services only when needed\n- Stop when not using to free RAM\n- OpenClaw works fine without them\n