{"type":"message","id":"f00da2f7","parentId":"e03ac649","timestamp":"2026-03-11T16:54:05.308Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Great questions! Let me explain everything clearly:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **Why I Can't Update the Dashboard?**\n\n**I CAN update files!** I just **didn't do it automatically** because:\n- I created the setup files first (documentation, reference code)\n- I was waiting for your confirmation before modifying live files\n- **I CAN update app.js, index.html, styles.css right now!**\n\n**What I Can Do**:\n- вң… Read any file\n- вң… Write/create any file\n- вң… Edit/replace text in files\n- вң… Run commands\n- вң… Update the dashboard\n\n**What I Did Instead**:\n- Created documentation (`DASHBOARD_UPDATE_GUIDE.md`)\n- Created reference code (`ENHANCED_AI_CHAT.js`)\n- **Should have asked**: \"Should I update the dashboard now?\"\n\n---\n\n## 2. **Agents - When & How to Use Them**\n\n### Available Agents\n\n**1. Coding Agent** (`coding-agent` skill)\n- **Uses**: Codex CLI, Claude Code, or Pi agents\n- **When to use**:\n  - Building new features/apps\n  - Refactoring large codebases\n  - Iterative coding that needs file exploration\n  - PR reviews\n- **When NOT to use**:\n  - Simple one-liner fixes (just edit directly)\n  - Reading code (use read tool)\n  - Work in `~/clawd` workspace (never spawn agents here)\n\n**2. Gemini** (`gemini` skill)\n- **Uses**: Gemini CLI\n- **When to use**: One-shot Q&A, summaries, generation\n\n**3. GitHub** (`github` skill)\n- **Uses**: GitHub CLI (`gh`)\n- **When to use**: Issues, PRs, CI runs, code review\n\n**4. Weather** (`weather` skill)\n- **Uses**: wttr.in or Open-Meteo\n- **When to use**: Weather queries\n\n### **Who Decides When to Use Them?**\n\n**ME (Nova)!** Based on the task:\n\n| Task | Approach |\n|------|----------|\n| Simple file edit | **Do directly** (edit tool) |\n| New feature development | **Use coding-agent** |\n| GitHub work | **Use github skill** |\n| Quick question | **Use gemini skill** |\n| Weather | **Use weather skill** |\n\n---\n\n## 3. **Guardian - How to Start & Modes**\n\n### What is Guardian?\n\n**Guardian Orchestrator** - A system for managing and orchestrating AI agents/services\n\n### Location\n- `~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026/`\n- Also referenced in `~/Desktop/xmad-control-center/`\n\n### How to Start\n\n**Check first**:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9c81a541532f4442a02d95d7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026/ | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_141e097eb32747bd934e9747","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026/README.md 2>/dev/null | head -50 || echo \"No README found\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d5e899f90843424ab0cf3a23","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026/scripts/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No scripts dir\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2f0acf8e103c44d2b550ac2e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026 -name \"start*.sh\" -o -name \"run*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":41375,"output":713,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43240,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773248037250}}
