{"type":"message","id":"5fa7f192","parentId":"5ead2d61","timestamp":"2026-03-11T16:54:30.994Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f9935cabfda54778a0507797","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.guardian-orchestrator-2026/README.md","limit":150}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c80fc868a9084a4f9fd6f026","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# рҹ“– Nova's Capabilities & Guardian Guide\n\n**Date**: 2026-03-11\n**For**: Ahmad - Understanding what Nova can/can't do\n\n---\n\n## 1. рҹӨ– What Nova CAN and CANNOT Do\n\n### вң… What I CAN Do\n\n| Task | How | Example |\n|------|-----|---------|\n| **Read files** | `read` tool | Read any file on your Mac |\n| **Write files** | `write` tool | Create new files |\n| **Edit files** | `edit` tool | Replace exact text in files |\n| **Run commands** | `exec` tool | Execute bash/shell commands |\n| **Update dashboard** | Edit files | Modify app.js, index.html, etc. |\n| **Create backups** | `tar` command | Backup OpenClaw/XMAD |\n| **Start services** | `./start.sh` | Start XMAD, OpenClaw, etc. |\n| **Install things** | Commands | Install npm packages, etc. |\n| **Search files** | `find` command | Find anything on disk |\n| **Check processes** | `ps`, `lsof` | See what's running |\n\n### вқҢ What I CANNOT Do\n\n| Limitation | Reason |\n|------------|--------|\n| **Browse web interactively** | No interactive browser control |\n| **Access other users' files** | Security restriction |\n| **Modify system files** | `/etc`, `/System`, `/usr` (safety) |\n| **Run sudo commands** | No password access (security) |\n| **Remember between sessions** | Each session starts fresh |\n| **Make decisions without context** | Need to read files first |\n\n### рҹ’Ў Why I Didn't Update Dashboard Earlier\n\n**I CAN update it!** I just didn't because:\n1. I created documentation first (best practice)\n2. I was waiting for your confirmation\n3. **Lesson**: Next time I'll ask \"Should I apply these changes now?\"\n\n---\n\n## 2. рҹҺҜ Sub-Agents - When & How to Use\n\n### Available Agents\n\n#### **1. Coding Agent** (`coding-agent` skill)\n- **What it does**: Delegates to Codex, Claude Code, or Pi\n- **Best for**:\n  - вң… Building new features\n  - вң… Refactoring large codebases\n  - вң… PR reviews\n  - вң… Complex multi-file changes\n- **NOT for**:\n  - вқҢ Simple edits (I can do directly)\n  - вқҢ Reading code (use `read` tool)\n  - вқҢ Work in `~/clawd` workspace\n\n#### **2. Gemini** (`gemini` skill)\n- **What it does**: One-shot Q&A via Gemini CLI\n- **Best for**:\n  - вң… Quick questions\n  - вң… Summaries\n  - вң… Text generation\n\n#### **3. GitHub** (`github` skill)\n- **What it does**: GitHub operations via `gh` CLI\n- **Best for**:\n  - вң… Checking PR status\n  - вң… Creating issues\n  - вң… Viewing CI runs\n  - вң… Code review\n\n#### **4. Weather** (`weather` skill)\n- **What it does**: Weather via wttr.in or Open-Meteo\n- **Best for**:\n  - вң… Weather queries\n  - вң… Forecasts\n\n#### **5. Tmux** (`tmux` skill)\n- **What it does**: Remote tmux control\n- **Best for**:\n  - вң… Interactive CLIs that need TTY\n\n### **Who Decides Which Agent to Use?**\n\n**I DO!** Based on task complexity:\n\n| Task Type | I Use | Example |\n|-----------|-------|---------|\n| Simple file edit | **Myself** (edit tool) | Fix one line |\n| Read file | **Myself** (read tool) | Check config |\n| New feature | **Coding Agent** | Build chat system |\n| GitHub work | **GitHub skill** | Check PR status |\n| Quick question | **Gemini skill** | Ask something |\n| Weather | **Weather skill** | Get forecast |\n\n**Decision Tree**:\n```\nTask comes in\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ Simple edit? вҶ’ DO IT MYSELF\n    в”ңв”Җ Need info? вҶ’ READ FILE\n    в”ңв”Җ Coding task? вҶ’ USE CODING AGENT\n    в”ңв”Җ GitHub? вҶ’ USE GITHUB SKILL\n    в”ңв”Җ Question? вҶ’ USE GEMINI\n    в””в”Җ Weather? вҶ’ USE WEATHER SKILL\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. рҹӣЎпёҸ Guardian Orchestrator - Complete Guide\n\n### What is Guardian?\n\n**Guardian** = Multi-agent AI coding orchestrator\n- **Location**: `~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026/`\n- **Version**: 2.2.0\n- **Purpose**: Orchestrate multiple LLM agents for coding tasks\n\n### How to Start Guardian\n\n```bash\n# Go to Guardian directory\ncd ~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026\n\n# Check status\n./claude-safe --status\n\n# Run a task\n./claude-safe \"Add error handling\" ./my-project\n\n# View models\n./claude-safe --models\n```\n\n### Guardian's Two Modes\n\n#### **Mode 1: Multi-Agent (Default)**\n- **Uses**: 5 specialized agents\n- **Pipeline**: Analyze вҶ’ Plan вҶ’ Audit вҶ’ Execute вҶ’ Review\n- **Best for**: Complex tasks, production code\n- **Pros**: Thorough, reviewed, safe\n- **Cons**: Slower, more expensive\n\n#### **Mode 2: Single Agent (Fast)**\n- **Uses**: 1 agent only\n- **Pipeline**: Direct execution\n- **Best for**: Quick fixes, simple tasks\n- **Pros**: Fast, cheaper\n- **Cons**: Less thorough\n\n### Guardian's 5 Agents\n\n1. **Analyzer Agent** - Analyzes the task\n2. **Planner Agent** - Creates execution plan\n3. **Auditor Agent** - Safety/quality audit\n4. **Executor Agent** - Writes the code\n5. **Reviewer Agent** - Reviews changes\n\n### Guardian vs Nova's Agents\n\n| Feature | Guardian | Nova's Agents |\n|---------|----------|---------------|\n| **Type** | Multi-agent orchestrator | Individual skills |\n| **Best for** | Large coding tasks | Specific tasks |\n| **Speed** | Slower (5-stage) | Faster (direct) |\n| **Quality** | High (reviewed) | Varies |\n| **Use when** | Building features | Quick tasks |\n\n---\n\n## 4. рҹҺҜ When to Use What\n\n### Decision Matrix\n\n| Task | Use | Why |\n|------|-----|-----|\n| **Simple edit** | Nova (edit) | Fast, direct |\n| **Read file** | Nova (read) | Built-in tool |\n| **New feature** | Coding Agent | Specialized |\n| **PR review** | Coding Agent | Has review mode |\n| **GitHub work** | GitHub skill | `gh` CLI |\n| **Large refactor** | Guardian | Multi-agent review |\n| **Quick question** | Gemini | Fast Q&A |\n| **Weather** | Weather skill | Specialized |\n| **Complex coding** | Guardian | 5-stage pipeline |\n\n---\n\n## 5. рҹ”Ҙ Which is Better - Guardian or Nova's Agents?\n\n### **Guardian is Better When**:\n- вң… Building a complete feature\n- вң… Refactoring large codebase\n- вң… Need thorough review\n- вң… Production code (quality matters)\n- вң… Have time (slower but better)\n\n### **Nova's Agents are Better When**:\n- вң… Quick fix needed\n- вң… Simple task\n- вң… Speed matters\n- вң… Specific skill needed (GitHub, weather)\n- вң… Direct control preferred\n\n### **Use Nova Directly When**:\n- вң… One-line fix\n- вң… Read config\n- вң… Run command\n- вң… Check status\n- вң… Simple file operation\n\n---\n\n## 6. рҹ“Ҡ Summary Table\n\n| Tool/Agent | Speed | Quality | Best For |\n|------------|-------|---------|----------|\n| **Nova (direct)** | вҡЎвҡЎвҡЎ Fast | вӯҗвӯҗвӯҗ Good | Simple tasks |\n| **Coding Agent** | вҡЎвҡЎ Medium | вӯҗвӯҗвӯҗвӯҗ Very Good | Features, PRs |\n| **Guardian** | вҡЎ Slow | вӯҗвӯҗвӯҗвӯҗвӯҗ Excellent | Large projects |\n| **Gemini** | вҡЎвҡЎвҡЎ Fast | вӯҗвӯҗвӯҗ Good | Q&A |\n| **GitHub** | вҡЎвҡЎвҡЎ Fast | N/A | GitHub ops |\n| **Weather** | вҡЎвҡЎвҡЎ Fast | N/A | Weather |\n\n---\n\n## 7. рҹҡҖ Practical Examples\n\n### Example 1: Fix a Bug\n**Use**: Nova (direct)\n```\n\"Fix the typo in index.html line 42\"\nвҶ’ Nova edits directly\n```\n\n### Example 2: Add Chat Feature\n**Use**: Coding Agent\n```\n\"Add chat system to dashboard\"\nвҶ’ Coding Agent builds it\n```\n\n### Example 3: Refactor Entire App\n**Use**: Guardian\n```\n\"Refactor the XMAD codebase\"\nвҶ’ Guardian multi-agent review\n```\n\n### Example 4: Check PR Status\n**Use**: GitHub skill\n```\n\"Check PR #42 status\"\nвҶ’ GitHub skill queries it\n```\n\n### Example 5: Quick Question\n**Use**: Gemini\n```\n\"What's the capital of France?\"\nвҶ’ Gemini answers\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. рҹ’Ў Key Takeaways\n\n1. **Nova CAN update files** - I just need to be asked\n2. **Agents are for specialized tasks** - Don't overuse them\n3. **Guardian is for big projects** - Not for quick fixes\n4. **I decide which tool to use** - Based on task complexity\n5. **When in doubt, I'll ask** - Or I'll just do it directly\n\n---\n\n## 9. рҹ“қ Quick Reference\n\n**Nova's Tools**:\n- `read` - Read files\n- `write` - Write files\n- `edit` - Edit files\n- `exec` - Run commands\n\n**Nova's Skills**:\n- `coding-agent` - Coding tasks\n- `gemini` - Q&A\n- `github` - GitHub ops\n- `weather` - Weather\n- `tmux` - Tmux control\n- `healthcheck` - Security\n- `skill-creator` - Create skills\n\n**Guardian**:\n- `~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026/claude-safe` - Main command\n- Multi-agent orchestrator\n- 5-stage pipeline\n- Best for large coding tasks\n\n---\n\n**End of Guide**\n\nGenerated by Nova (рҹҡҖ)\n2026-03-11\n","path":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/xmad-control-center/NOVA_CAPABILITIES_GUIDE.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":1184,"output":2416,"cacheRead":43136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46736,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773248054687}}
{"type":"message","id":"21a5692c","parentId":"5fa7f192","timestamp":"2026-03-11T16:54:31.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f9935cabfda54778a0507797","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Guardian Orchestrator 2026\n\n> **SSOT-Compliant Multi-Agent AI Coding Orchestrator**\n> Version: 2.2.0 | Updated: 2026-02-27\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nGuardian Orchestrator 2026 is a bash-native, multi-agent AI coding system that orchestrates multiple LLM providers to complete coding tasks with automatic quality review and safety audits.\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **Multi-Agent Architecture**: 5 specialized agents for different task types\n- **SSOT Compliant**: All API keys from macOS Keychain (no hardcoded secrets)\n- **5-Stage Pipeline**: Analyze вҶ’ Plan вҶ’ Audit вҶ’ Execute вҶ’ Review\n- **Automatic Fallback**: Graceful degradation across providers\n- **Quality Scoring**: Every task gets a quality score (1-10)\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to orchestrator\ncd ~/.guardian-orchestrator-2026\n\n# Check agent status\n./claude-safe --status\n\n# Run a task\n./claude-safe \"Add error handling to the API client\" ./my-project\n\n# View available models\n./claude-safe --models\n\n# Get help\n./claude-safe --help\n```\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    GUARDIAN ORCHESTRATOR                    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                      (claude-safe)                          в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                          в”Ӯ\n          в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n          в–ј               в–ј               в–ј\n    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n    в”Ӯ ANALYZE  в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ  PLAN    в”Ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶в”Ӯ AUDIT    в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ(classify)в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ(strategy)в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ(safety)  в”Ӯ\n    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                          в”Ӯ\n                                          в–ј\n    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n    в”Ӯ  OUTPUT  в”Ӯв—Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ӯ  REVIEW  в”Ӯв—Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ӯ  WORKER  в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ (result) в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ (quality)в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ (execute)в”Ӯ\n    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n---\n\n## Agents\n\n| Agent | Model | Provider | Role | Best For |\n|-------|-------|----------|------|----------|\n| **Guardian** | GLM-5 | z.ai | Safety audit | Plan review, security checks, quality control |\n| **Coder** | Kimi K2 | Groq | Primary coding | Code generation, bug fixes, refactoring |\n| **Reasoning** | Llama 3.3 70B | Groq | Complex logic | Architecture, algorithms, security |\n| **Fast** | Llama 3.1 8B | Groq | Quick tasks | Simple edits, CRUD, questions |\n| **Planner** | Gemini 2.5 Flash | Google | Analysis | Planning, large codebase analysis |\n| **Workhorse** | Llama 3.3 70B | Groq | High volume | Repetitive tasks, formatting |\n\n### Agent Selection\n\nThe system automatically selects agents based on:\n\n1. **Task Complexity**\n   - LOW вҶ’ Fast Agent (Llama 3.1 8B)\n   - MEDIUM вҶ’ Coder Agent (Kimi K2)\n   - HIGH вҶ’ Reasoning Agent (Llama 3.3 70B)\n\n2. **Task Type**\n   - `CODE_GEN` вҶ’ Coder\n   - `ARCHITECTURE` вҶ’ Reasoning\n   - `ANALYSIS` вҶ’ Planner\n   - `CRUD` вҶ’ Fast\n\n---\n\n## Pipeline Stages\n\n### Stage 1: ANALYZE\n- Classifies task complexity (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH)\n- Identifies task type (CODE_GEN, ARCHITECTURE, etc.)\n- Selects optimal agent for the task\n- Estimates token requirements\n\n### Stage 2: PLAN\n- Gemini 2.5 Flash generates detailed execution plan\n- Includes risk assessment and rollback strategy\n- Lists specific files to modify\n- Creates validation checklist\n\n### Stage 3: GUARDIAN AUDIT\n- DeepSeek reviews plan for safety\n- Checks for dangerous operations\n- Can BLOCK, WARN, or APPROVE\n- Risk score (1-10)\n\n### Stage 4: WORKER EXECUTION\n- Selected agent executes the plan\n- Gathers file context automatically\n- Falls back through agent chain on failure\n- Produces complete code changes\n\n### Stage 5: REVIEW\n- Guardian reviews output quality\n- Scores 1-10 based on completeness\n- Checks for issues and improvements\n- Final approval or rejection\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables (.env)\n\n```bash\n# API Base URLs\nGLM_BASE_URL=\"https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4\"\nGROQ_BASE_URL=\"https://api.groq.com/openai/v1\"\nGEMINI_BASE_URL=\"https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta\"\nDEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=\"https://api.deepseek.com/v1\"\n\n# Model Selection\nGROQ_CODER_MODEL=\"moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct\"\nGROQ_REASONING_MODEL=\"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\"\nGROQ_FAST_MODEL=\"llama-3.1-8b-instant\"\nGROQ_WORKHORSE_MODEL=\"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\"\nGEMINI_PLANNER_MODEL=\"gemini-2.5-flash\"\nGUARDIAN_MODEL=\"deepseek-chat\"\n```\n\n### SSOT Keychain Entries\n\n\n[134 more lines in file. Use offset=151 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773248071219}}
