{"type":"message","id":"18fa49b3","parentId":"752a53bd","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:37:51.702Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-11 22:24:53 GMT+4] Exec completed (young-sh, code 0) :: Memory Usage: <span id=\"memory-usage\">-</span></div> <div>CPU Load: <span id=\"cpu-load\">-</span></div> <div>Disk Usage: <span id=\"disk-usage\">-</span></div> </div> <div class=\"proвҖҰ\nSystem: [2026-03-11 22:26:09 GMT+4] Exec completed (gentle-c, code 0) :: в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ Project: /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/xmad-control-center/packages/legacy/ Dry-run: No рҹ“Ұ Files to write: 2 вҡЎ Commands to run: 0 рҹ“қ Applying file changesвҖҰ вҖҰ\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2A9AA5A3FC914CA6FCFE\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+971504042000\",\n  \"sender\": \"Golden Cruise Restaurant\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Golden Cruise Restaurant (+971504042000)\",\n  \"id\": \"+971504042000\",\n  \"name\": \"Golden Cruise Restaurant\",\n  \"e164\": \"+971504042000\"\n}\n```\n\nWait . \nWhy not we create a sample in the same glass liquid project"}],"timestamp":1773254271694}}
{"type":"message","id":"9e91c7c4","parentId":"18fa49b3","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:38:01.084Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent idea! Let me create a proper dashboard using the **ein-ui** liquid glass components project you already have. That way we get beautiful, professional glassmorphism styling right from the start."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eed1a13e12ef45afa4543774","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/ein-ui/README.md","limit":100}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_043a99dae6534c52be0acc6d","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# рҹҺЁ XMAD Dashboard with ein-ui\n\n**Idea**: Use the existing ein-ui project for beautiful liquid glass components\n\n## Plan:\n\n### Step 1: Explore ein-ui\n- Check available components\n- Copy component structure\n- Use glassy liquid design system\n\n### Step 2: Create XMAD Dashboard\n- New dashboard using ein-ui components\n- Small SVG icons (12-16px)\n- Professional glassmorphism\n- Clean, modern design\n\n### Step 3: Features\n- Mini widgets\n- Cards with glass effect\n- Proper navigation\n- Status indicators\n- All functionality preserved\n\n---\n\n**This is the right approach - using a proven design system!**","path":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/xmad-control-center/EIN_UI_PLAN.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e1fb8bd7d4d1469088c44dd7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/ein-ui && ls -la src/components/ui/ | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_72e472ec52c74cc9b03b2d77","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/Desktop/ein-ui/package.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":39365,"output":292,"cacheRead":60160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99817,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773254271698}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b0a8bc0","parentId":"9e91c7c4","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:38:01.272Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_eed1a13e12ef45afa4543774","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Ein UI вҖ” Liquid Glass Components (Shadcn Registry)\n\n[![Demo](https://img.shields.io/badge/demo-Demo%20Site-brightgreen)](https://ui.eindev.ir)\n[![Registry](https://img.shields.io/badge/registry-JSON-brightgreen?style=flat)](/r/registry.json)\n[![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-1.0.0-blue?style=flat)](#key-features)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-ISC-blue?style=flat)](/LICENCE)\n[![TypeScript](https://img.shields.io/badge/TypeScript-вң”-blue?style=flat)](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)\n[![Next.js%2016](https://img.shields.io/badge/Next.js-v16-black?style=flat)](https://nextjs.org/docs)\n[![Tailwind%20CSS](https://img.shields.io/badge/Tailwind%20v4-%20%20-06B6D4?style=flat&logo=tailwindcss&logoColor=white)](https://tailwindcss.com/)\n\n<img src=\"public/screenshot.png\" alt=\"Next.js 16 Starter\"  style=\"display: block; margin: 0 auto; border-radius: 15px; max-width: 80%;\" />\n<br/>\n\nWelcome! Ein UI is a collection of beautiful, ready-made \"liquid glass\" components that you can preview, copy, and use in your website or app. This guide explains how to preview the components, get code snippets, and add a component to your project вҖ” no developer knowledge required.\n\nвң… Great for: designers and frontend developers who want shareable, copy-and-paste UI components\nwith consistent design patterns and built-in accessibility.\n\n---\n\n## Key features\n\n- Collection of handcrafted, accessible components built on top of Radix UI primitives and\n  Tailwind CSS v4 (TypeScript + React 19).\n- Components are distributed using the shadcn registry format вҖ” components are easy to install\n  into other projects using the `shadcn` CLI.\n- Built-in documentation site and component previews (Next.js 16 + app router)\n- Example page templates / blocks (e.g., Admin Panel) to showcase layout patterns.\n- Zod validation examples and server/client component patterns for modern full-stack apps.\n\n---\n\n## Quick links\n\n- **Preview docs**: [Live preview](https://ui.eindev.ir)\n- **Registry JSON**: [Registry JSON](/r/registry.json)\n- **Try components**: For details, see `app/docs/components/*`\n\n---\n\n## Get started (local development)\n\nRequirements: Node.js 20+ (recommended), pnpm (optional but used in this repo), or npm/yarn.\n\n1. Clone the repo\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/ehsanghaffar/ein-ui.git\ncd ein-ui-shadcn-register\n```\n\n2 Install dependencies\n\n```bash\n# using pnpm\npnpm install\n\n# or using npm\nnpm install\n\n# or yarn\nyarn install\n```\n\n3 Run development server\n\n```bash\npnpm dev\n# or npm run dev\n# App runs on http://localhost:3000\n```\n\n### Using Next.js 16.1.0 bundle analyzer\n\nTo analyze your Next.js bundle, you can use the built-in experimental analyzer:\n\n```bash\npnpm analyze\n# or npm run analyze\n```\n\n## Contributing\n\nContributions welcome! Please read [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](./CONTRIBUTING.md) and follow the issue and PR templates when submitting work.\n\n- Run `pnpm lint` to check code style\n- New components should include comprehensive examples under `app/docs/components/*` and should declare any required `dependencies` in `registry.json`\n\nWhere to find guidance:\n\n- Docs pages in the repo (`https://ui.eindev.ir/docs`) include live previews and code snippets.\n- Use `shadcn` registry format to make your component discoverable via the CLI.\n\nPlease also see `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md` and `SECURITY.md` for reporting guidelines.\n\n---\n\n## Support and help\n\n- If the repository is hosted on GitHub, open an issue on the repo or create a Pull Request to propose changes\n\n[13 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773254281269}}
