{"type":"message","id":"da613f98","parentId":"d2dc4ab1","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:52:29.920Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0a688eb9a95849e6b39c3b2d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session brisk-coral, pid 48167). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"brisk-coral","pid":48167,"startedAt":1773255139913,"cwd":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.openclaw/workspace","tail":""},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773255149917}}
{"type":"message","id":"255d6df7","parentId":"da613f98","timestamp":"2026-03-11T18:52:30.342Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_77611b9ff6514028bf0e470c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Infisical is a simple, end-to-end encrypted service that enables teams to sync and manage their environment variables across their development life cycle.\n\nUsage:\n  infisical [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  agent           Used to launch a client daemon that streamlines authentication and secret retrieval processes in various environments\n  bootstrap       Used to bootstrap your Infisical instance\n  cert-manager    Certificate management commands\n  dynamic-secrets Used to list dynamic secrets\n  export          Used to export environment variables to a file\n  gateway         Run the Infisical gateway or manage its systemd service\n  help            Help about any command\n  init            Used to connect your local project with Infisical project\n  kmip            Used to manage KMIP servers\n  login           Login into your Infisical account\n  pam             PAM-related commands\n  proxy           Used to run Infisical proxy server\n  relay           Relay-related commands\n  reset           Used to delete all Infisical related data on your machine\n  run             Used to inject environments variables into your application process\n  scan            Scan for leaked secrets in git history, directories, and files\n  secrets         Used to create, read update and delete secrets\n  service-token   Manage service tokens\n  ssh             Used to issue SSH credentials\n  token           Manage your access tokens\n  user            Used to manage local user credentials\n  vault           Used to manage where your Infisical login token is saved on your machine\n\nFlags:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":421,"aggregated":"Infisical is a simple, end-to-end encrypted service that enables teams to sync and manage their environment variables across their development life cycle.\n\nUsage:\n  infisical [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  agent           Used to launch a client daemon that streamlines authentication and secret retrieval processes in various environments\n  bootstrap       Used to bootstrap your Infisical instance\n  cert-manager    Certificate management commands\n  dynamic-secrets Used to list dynamic secrets\n  export          Used to export environment variables to a file\n  gateway         Run the Infisical gateway or manage its systemd service\n  help            Help about any command\n  init            Used to connect your local project with Infisical project\n  kmip            Used to manage KMIP servers\n  login           Login into your Infisical account\n  pam             PAM-related commands\n  proxy           Used to run Infisical proxy server\n  relay           Relay-related commands\n  reset           Used to delete all Infisical related data on your machine\n  run             Used to inject environments variables into your application process\n  scan            Scan for leaked secrets in git history, directories, and files\n  secrets         Used to create, read update and delete secrets\n  service-token   Manage service tokens\n  ssh             Used to issue SSH credentials\n  token           Manage your access tokens\n  user            Used to manage local user credentials\n  vault           Used to manage where your Infisical login token is saved on your machine\n\nFlags:","cwd":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773255150339}}
