{"type":"message","id":"521ee2cb","parentId":"8d9aab4a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:37:34.459Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0f96646345804b7d9f3a4aee","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ahmadabdullah/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-12.md","content":"# Memory Log - 2026-03-12\n\n## XMAD Control Deployment\n\n**Status**: вң… Successfully Deployed\n\n**User Request**:\n- Clone template-v1 (simple version only, NOT the Shadi project)\n- Rename to xmad-control\n- Deploy to Vercel\n- Configure auto-deploy\n- NO auth, NO database, NO Supabase, NO audit systems\n- Simple startup project with minimum UI packages\n\n**What Happened**:\n1. The template-v1 repo actually contains the Shadi project (full-featured with auth, Supabase, dashboards)\n2. User wanted the SIMPLE version (1 page, minimal dependencies)\n3. After multiple failed attempts to clean the Shadi project, I created a minimal Next.js project from scratch\n\n**Solution**:\n- Created fresh minimal Next.js 15 + React 18 + Tailwind CSS project\n- Simple home page with \"XMAD Control Center v4.0\" title\n- No Supabase, no auth, no audit systems\n- Pushed to https://github.com/xmad11/xmad-control\n- Deployed to https://xmad-control.vercel.app\n- Auto-deploy configured (GitHub вҶ’ Vercel)\n\n**Project Structure**:\n```\nxmad-control/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ app/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ globals.css\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ layout.tsx\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ page.tsx\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ package.json\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ tsconfig.json\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ tailwind.config.js\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ postcss.config.js\nв””в”Җв”Җ next.config.js\n```\n\n**Key Files Created**:\n- package.json: Next 15, React 18, Tailwind CSS 3, minimal dependencies\n- app/page.tsx: Simple home page\n- app/layout.tsx: Root layout with metadata\n- app/globals.css: Tailwind imports + custom styles\n\n**Deployment Details**:\n- Vercel Team: ahmad-s-projects-7e32bc62\n- Auto-deploy: Enabled (main branch вҶ’ production)\n- Build time: ~24 seconds\n- Framework: Next.js 15.5.12\n\n**Important URLs**:\n- GitHub: https://github.com/xmad11/xmad-control\n- Production: https://xmad-control.vercel.app\n- Inspect: https://vercel.com/ahmad-s-projects-7e32bc62/xmad-control\n\n**Lessons Learned**:\n- The template-v1 repo IS the Shadi project (not a simple template)\n- User wanted minimal startup project, NOT the full-featured app\n- Auto-deploy works automatically when GitHub repo is connected to Vercel\n- PostCSS config must use CommonJS format for Next.js compatibility\n\n**User Preferences**:\n- Prefers simple, minimal templates\n- Does NOT want audit systems, Supabase, or auth by default\n- Wants to add features only when explicitly requested\n- Direct communication, no filler explanations\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":55661,"output":651,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57464,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773265044047}}
